data.label: Title
data.comment: A name given to the resource.

data.label: Creator
data.comment: An entity primarily responsible for making the resource.

data.label: Subject
data.comment: The topic of the resource.

data.label: Description
data.comment: An account of the resource.

data.label: Publisher
data.comment: An entity responsible for making the resource available.

data.label: Contributor
data.comment: An entity responsible for making contributions to the resource.

data.label: Date
data.comment: A point or period of time associated with an event in the lifecycle of the resource.

data.label: Type
data.comment: The nature or genre of the resource.

data.label: Format
data.comment: The file format, physical medium, or dimensions of the resource.

data.label: Identifier
data.comment: An unambiguous reference to the resource within a given context.

data.label: Source
data.comment: A related resource from which the described resource is derived.

data.label: Language
data.comment: A language of the resource.

data.label: Relation
data.comment: A related resource.

data.label: Coverage
data.comment: The spatial or temporal topic of the resource, the spatial applicability of the resource, or the jurisdiction under which the resource is relevant.

data.label: Rights
data.comment: Information about rights held in and over the resource.

data.label: Audience
data.comment: A class of entity for whom the resource is intended or useful.

data.label: Alternative Title
data.comment: An alternative name for the resource.

data.label: Table Of Contents
data.comment: A list of subunits of the resource.

data.label: Abstract
data.comment: A summary of the resource.

data.label: Date Created
data.comment: Date of creation of the resource.

data.label: Date Valid
data.comment: Date (often a range) of validity of a resource.

data.label: Date Available
data.comment: Date (often a range) that the resource became or will become available.

data.label: Date Issued
data.comment: Date of formal issuance (e.g., publication) of the resource.

data.label: Date Modified
data.comment: Date on which the resource was changed.

data.label: Extent
data.comment: The size or duration of the resource.

data.label: Medium
data.comment: The material or physical carrier of the resource.

data.label: Is Version Of
data.comment: A related resource of which the described resource is a version, edition, or adaptation.

data.label: Has Version
data.comment: A related resource that is a version, edition, or adaptation of the described resource.

data.label: Is Replaced By
data.comment: A related resource that supplants, displaces, or supersedes the described resource.

data.label: Replaces
data.comment: A related resource that is supplanted, displaced, or superseded by the described resource.

data.label: Is Required By
data.comment: A related resource that requires the described resource to support its function, delivery, or coherence.

data.label: Requires
data.comment: A related resource that is required by the described resource to support its function, delivery, or coherence.

data.label: Is Part Of
data.comment: A related resource in which the described resource is physically or logically included.

data.label: Has Part
data.comment: A related resource that is included either physically or logically in the described resource.

data.label: Is Referenced By
data.comment: A related resource that references, cites, or otherwise points to the described resource.

data.label: References
data.comment: A related resource that is referenced, cited, or otherwise pointed to by the described resource.

data.label: Is Format Of
data.comment: A related resource that is substantially the same as the described resource, but in another format.

data.label: Has Format
data.comment: A related resource that is substantially the same as the pre-existing described resource, but in another format.

data.label: Conforms To
data.comment: An established standard to which the described resource conforms.

data.label: Spatial Coverage
data.comment: Spatial characteristics of the resource.

data.label: Temporal Coverage
data.comment: Temporal characteristics of the resource.

data.label: Mediator
data.comment: An entity that mediates access to the resource and for whom the resource is intended or useful.

data.label: Date Accepted
data.comment: Date of acceptance of the resource.

data.label: Date Copyrighted
data.comment: Date of copyright.

data.label: Date Submitted
data.comment: Date of submission of the resource.

data.label: Audience Education Level
data.comment: A class of entity, defined in terms of progression through an educational or training context, for which the described resource is intended.

data.label: Access Rights
data.comment: Information about who can access the resource or an indication of its security status.

data.label: Bibliographic Citation
data.comment: A bibliographic reference for the resource.

data.label: License
data.comment: A legal document giving official permission to do something with the resource.

data.label: Rights Holder
data.comment: A person or organization owning or managing rights over the resource.

data.label: Provenance
data.comment: A statement of any changes in ownership and custody of the resource since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, integrity, and interpretation.

data.label: Instructional Method
data.comment: A process, used to engender knowledge, attitudes and skills, that the described resource is designed to support.

data.label: Accrual Method
data.comment: The method by which items are added to a collection.

data.label: Accrual Periodicity
data.comment: The frequency with which items are added to a collection.

data.label: Accrual Policy
data.comment: The policy governing the addition of items to a collection.

data.label: affirmedBy
data.comment: A legal decision that affirms a ruling.

data.label: annotates
data.comment: Critical or explanatory note for a Document.

data.label: list of authors
data.comment: An ordered list of authors. Normally, this list is seen as a priority list that order authors by importance.

data.label: cited by
data.comment:
Relates a document to another document that cites the
first document.

data.label: cites
data.comment:
Relates a document to another document that is cited
by the first document as reference, comment, review, quotation or for
another purpose.

data.label: list of contributors
data.comment: An ordered list of contributors. Normally, this list is seen as a priority list that order contributors by importance.

data.label: court
data.comment: A court associated with a legal document; for example, that which issues a decision.

data.label: degree
data.comment: The thesis degree.

data.label: director
data.comment: A Film director.

data.label: distributor
data.comment: Distributor of a document or a collection of documents.

data.label: editor
data.comment: A person having managerial and sometimes policy-making responsibility for the editorial part of a publishing firm or of a newspaper, magazine, or other publication.

data.label: list of editors
data.comment: An ordered list of editors. Normally, this list is seen as a priority list that order editors by importance.

data.label: interviewee
data.comment: An agent that is interviewed by another agent.

data.label: interviewer
data.comment: An agent that interview another agent.

data.label: issuer
data.comment: An entity responsible for issuing often informally published documents such as press releases, reports, etc.

data.label: organizer
data.comment: The organizer of an event; includes conference organizers, but also government agencies or other bodies that are responsible for conducting hearings.

data.label: owner
data.comment: Owner of a document or a collection of documents.

data.label: presented at
data.comment: Relates a document to an event; for example, a paper to a conference.

data.label: presents
data.comment: Relates an event to associated documents; for example, conference to a paper.

data.label: producer
data.comment: Producer of a document or a collection of documents.

data.label: recipient
data.comment: An agent that receives a communication document.

data.label: reproducedIn
data.comment: The resource in which another resource is reproduced.

data.label: reversedBy
data.comment: A legal decision that reverses a ruling.

data.label: review of
data.comment: Relates a review document to a reviewed thing (resource, item, etc.).

data.label: status
data.comment: The publication status of (typically academic) content.

data.label: subsequentLegalDecision
data.comment: A legal decision on appeal that takes action on a case (affirming it, reversing it, etc.).

data.label: transcript of
data.comment: Relates a document to some transcribed original.

data.label: translation of
data.comment: Relates a translated document to the original document.

data.label: translator
data.comment: A person who translates written document from one language to another.

data.label: abstract
data.comment: A summary of the resource.

data.label: date argued
data.comment: The date on which a legal case is argued before a court. Date is of format xsd:date

data.label: chapter
data.comment: An chapter number

data.label: content
data.comment: This property is for a plain-text rendering of the content of a Document. While the plain-text content of an entire document could be described by this property.

data.label: edition
data.comment: The name defining a special edition of a document. Normally its a literal value composed of a version number and words.

data.label: issue
data.comment: An issue number

data.label: locator
data.comment: A description (often numeric) that locates an item within a containing document or collection.

data.label: number of pages
data.comment: The number of pages contained in a document

data.label: number of volumes
data.comment: The number of volumes contained in a collection of documents (usually a series, periodical, etc.).

data.label: number
data.comment: A generic item or document number. Not to be confused with issue number.

data.label: page end
data.comment: Ending page number within a continuous page range.

data.label: page start
data.comment: Starting page number within a continuous page range.

data.label: pages
data.comment: A string of non-contiguous page spans that locate a Document within a Collection. Example: 23-25, 34, 54-56. For continuous page ranges, use the pageStart and pageEnd properties.

data.label: prefix name
data.comment: The prefix of a name

data.label: section
data.comment: A section number

data.label: short title
data.comment: The abbreviation of a title.

data.label: suffix name
data.comment: The suffix of a name

data.label: uri
data.comment: Universal Resource Identifier of a document

data.label: volume
data.comment: A volume number

data.comment: A  personal mailbox, ie. an Internet mailbox associated with exactly one owner, the first owner of this mailbox. This is a 'static inverse functional property', in that  there is (across time and change) at most one individual that ever has any particular value for foaf:mbox.

data.label: Agent

data.label: Agent Class

data.label: Bibliographic Resource

data.label: File Format

data.label: Frequency

data.label: Jurisdiction

data.label: License Document
data.comment: A legal document giving official permission to do something with a Resource.

data.label: Linguistic System
data.comment: A system of signs, symbols, sounds, gestures, or rules used in communication.

data.label: Location

data.label: Location, Period, or Jurisdiction
data.comment: A location, period of time, or jurisdiction.

data.label: Media Type

data.label: Media Type or Extent
data.comment: A media type or extent.

data.label: Method of Instruction
data.comment: A process that is used to engender knowledge, attitudes, and skills.

data.label: Method of Accrual
data.comment: A method by which resources are added to a collection.

data.label: Period of Time
data.comment: An interval of time that is named or defined by its start and end dates.

data.label: Physical Medium
data.comment: A physical material or carrier.

data.label: Physical Resource
data.comment: A material thing.

data.label: Policy
data.comment: A plan or course of action by an authority, intended to influence and determine decisions, actions, and other matters.

data.label: Provenance Statement
data.comment: A statement of any changes in ownership and custody of a resource since its creation that are significant for its authenticity, integrity, and interpretation.

data.label: Rights Statement
data.comment: A statement about the intellectual property rights (IPR) held in or over a Resource, a legal document giving official permission to do something with a resource, or a statement about access rights.

data.label: Size or Duration
data.comment: A dimension or extent, or a time taken to play or execute.

data.label: Standard
data.comment: A basis for comparison; a reference point against which other things can be evaluated.

data.label: Collection
data.comment: An aggregation of resources.

data.label: Dataset
data.comment: Data encoded in a defined structure.

data.label: Event
data.comment: A non-persistent, time-based occurrence.

data.label: Image
data.comment: A visual representation other than text.

data.label: Interactive Resource
data.comment: A resource requiring interaction from the user to be understood, executed, or experienced.

data.label: Service
data.comment: A system that provides one or more functions.

data.label: Software
data.comment: A computer program in source or compiled form.

data.label: Sound
data.comment: A resource primarily intended to be heard.

data.label: Text
data.comment: A resource consisting primarily of words for reading.

data.label: Physical Object
data.comment: An inanimate, three-dimensional object or substance.

data.label: Still Image
data.comment: A static visual representation.

data.label: Moving Image
data.comment: A series of visual representations imparting an impression of motion when shown in succession.

data.label: Academic Article
data.comment: A scholarly academic article, typically published in a journal.

data.label: Article
data.comment: A written composition in prose, usually nonfiction, on a specific topic, forming an independent part of a book or other publication, as a newspaper or magazine.

data.label: audio document
data.comment: An audio document; aka record.

data.label: audio-visual document
data.comment: An audio-visual document; film, video, and so forth.

data.label: Bill
data.comment: Draft legislation presented for discussion to a legal body.

data.label: Book
data.comment: A written or printed work of fiction or nonfiction, usually on sheets of paper fastened or bound together within covers.

data.label: Book Section
data.comment: A section of a book.

data.label: Brief
data.comment: A written argument submitted to a court.

data.label: Chapter
data.comment: A chapter of a book.

data.label: Code
data.comment: A collection of statutes.

data.label: Collected Document
data.comment: A document that simultaneously contains other documents.

data.label: Collection
data.comment: A collection of Documents or Collections

data.label: Conference
data.comment: A meeting for consultation or discussion.

data.label: Court Reporter
data.comment: A collection of legal cases.

data.label: Document
data.comment: A document (noun) is a bounded physical representation of body of information designed with the capacity (and usually intent) to communicate. A document may manifest symbolic, diagrammatic or sensory-representational information.

data.label: document part
data.comment: a distinct part of a larger document or collected document.

data.label: Document Status
data.comment: The status of the publication of a document.

data.label: Edited Book
data.comment: An edited book.

data.label: EMail
data.comment: A written communication addressed to a person or organization and transmitted electronically.

data.label: Excerpt
data.comment: A passage selected from a larger work.

data.label: Film
data.comment: aka movie.

data.label: Hearing
data.comment: An instance or a session in which testimony and arguments are presented, esp. before an official, as a judge in a lawsuit.

data.label: Image
data.comment: A document that presents visual or diagrammatic information.

data.label: Interview
data.comment: A formalized discussion between two or more people.

data.label: Issue
data.comment: something that is printed or published and distributed, esp. a given number of a periodical

data.label: Journal
data.comment: A periodical of scholarly journal Articles.

data.label: Legal Case Document
data.comment: A document accompanying a legal case.

data.label: Decision
data.comment: A document containing an authoritative determination (as a decree or judgment) made after consideration of facts or law.

data.label: Legal Document
data.comment: A legal document; for example, a court decision, a brief, and so forth.

data.label: Legislation
data.comment: A legal document proposing or enacting a law or a group of laws.

data.label: Letter
data.comment: A written or printed communication addressed to a person or organization and usually transmitted by mail.

data.label: Magazine
data.comment: A periodical of magazine Articles. A magazine is a publication that is issued periodically, usually bound in a paper cover, and typically contains essays, stories, poems, etc., by many writers, and often photographs and drawings, frequently specializing in a particular subject or area, as hobbies, news, or sports.

data.label: Manual
data.comment: A small reference book, especially one giving instructions.

data.label: Manuscript
data.comment: An unpublished Document, which may also be submitted to a publisher for publication.

data.label: Map
data.comment: A graphical depiction of geographic features.

data.label: Multivolume Book
data.comment: A loose, thematic, collection of Documents, often Books.

data.label: Newspaper
data.comment: A periodical of documents, usually issued daily or weekly, containing current news, editorials, feature articles, and usually advertising.

data.label: Note
data.comment: Notes or annotations about a resource.

data.label: Patent
data.comment: A document describing the exclusive right granted by a government to an inventor to manufacture, use, or sell an invention for a certain number of years.

data.label: Performance
data.comment: A public performance.

data.label: Periodical
data.comment: A group of related documents issued at regular intervals.

data.label: Personal Communication
data.comment: A communication between an agent and one or more specific recipients.

data.label: Personal Communication Document
data.comment: A personal communication manifested in some document.

data.label: Proceedings
data.comment: A compilation of documents published from an event, such as a conference.

data.label: Quote
data.comment: An excerpted collection of words.

data.label: Reference Source
data.comment: A document that presents authoritative reference information, such as a dictionary or encylopedia .

data.label: Report
data.comment: A document describing an account or statement describing in detail an event, situation, or the like, usually as the result of observation, inquiry, etc..

data.label: Series
data.comment: A loose, thematic, collection of Documents, often Books.

data.label: Slide
data.comment: A slide in a slideshow

data.label: Slideshow
data.comment: A presentation of a series of slides, usually presented in front of an audience with written text and images.

data.label: Standard
data.comment: A document describing a standard

data.label: Statute
data.comment: A bill enacted into law.

data.label: Thesis
data.comment: A document created to summarize research findings associated with the completion of an academic degree.

data.label: Thesis degree
data.comment: The academic degree of a Thesis

data.label: Webpage
data.comment: A web page is an online document available (at least initially) on the world wide web. A web page is written first and foremost to appear on the web, as distinct from other online resources such as books, manuscripts or audio documents which use the web primarily as a distribution mechanism alongside other more traditional methods such as print.

data.label: Website
data.comment: A group of Webpages accessible on the Web.

data.label: Workshop
data.comment: A seminar, discussion group, or the like, that emphasizes zxchange of ideas and the demonstration and application of techniques, skills, etc.

data.label: Label Property
data.comment: A foaf:LabelProperty is any RDF property with texual values that serve as labels.
